  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "So far, most approaches to explainable AI focus on post-hoc explanations 114 that are generated with a fully trained model.",
    "However, these models are not trained for generating faithful attributions, so it is not ensured that the post-hoc explanations are interpretable 115.",
    "Hence, other ways of directly encoding interpretable parts into the model, for instance through hybrid modeling, may be more suitable 116.",
    "An interesting approach here is building up agent-based modeling, where stakeholders are represented as independent agents interacting with each other.",
    "Each agent could be an AI, with learned behavior, allowing to model socio-economic systems directly from raw data 117, 118.On a more general note, and from a practical perspective, taking action is often hindered by political and administrative constraints, unrelated to scientific evidence and technological options."
  ],
